    <li>
      <p>
        <xref ref="proof-cons-2"></xref>
        An integer solution to the equation <m>4x_1+5x_2=1</m> is
        <me>
          (x_1,x_2)=(-1,1)
        </me>.
        Hence we have a particular solution
        <me>
          (x_1,x_2)=(-n,n)
        </me>
        in case of the equation <m>4x_1+5x_2=n</m>.
        It is now clear that all solutions can be obtained from the parametrization
        <me>
          (-n-5t,n+4t) t\in\mathbb{Z}
        </me>.
        To have non-negative solutions one needs
